      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup, boundary conditions, and material assignments performed prior to simulation runs.",
      "rationale": "An independent analyst reviewed the model setup, boundary conditions, contact definitions, and material assignments for each of the three FEA implementations. Discrepancies were resolved before final simulation runs. Required level 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic material model for titanium alloy components justified by strain gauge measurements confirming elastic regime at all test load levels; contact mechanics formulation validated against Hertzian benchmarks.",
      "rationale": "Strain gauge measurements on representative constructs confirmed that all components remained in the elastic regime throughout the F1717 test protocol. A linear elastic constitutive model is therefore appropriate. Coulomb friction contact with coefficient 0.2 was selected based on literature values for titanium-on-titanium interfaces. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties (E, nu) measured from coupon specimens cut from the same lot as the test constructs; geometric dimensions measured by CMM with traceability to NIST standards.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and Poisson's ratio for Ti-6Al-4V ELI were measured from five coupon specimens machined from the same material lot as the pedicle screw constructs. Geometric dimensions were measured by coordinate measuring machine. Measurement uncertainty was propagated through the FEA inputs. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs tested; samples drawn from production lots with documented traceability; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to design drawings.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories. All specimens were drawn from production lots with full material and dimensional traceability. CMM inspection confirmed conformance to design drawings within specified tolerances. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two independent load configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration. Although this represents the standard regulatory test condition, only one load configuration was evaluated, which limits coverage of the full clinical loading envelope. Achieved level 2 is below the required level 3; this shortfall is acknowledged as a limitation of the current validation scope and will be addressed in a follow-on validation study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate the F1717 test fixture kinematics; fixture compliance characterized and incorporated into the model.",
      "rationale": "The FEA model explicitly represents the ASTM F1717 test fixture geometry, including the superior and inferior loading blocks, the UHMWPE blocks, and the titanium rods. Fixture compliance was measured and incorporated as elastic foundation boundary conditions. Agreement between FEA and experimental load-displacement curves confirms boundary condition equivalency. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; acceptance bound E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs; mean absolute percentage error < 10%.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison was performed using the ASME V&V 40 validation metric E/uval, where E is the model-experiment difference and uval is the combined validation uncertainty. All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) yielded E/uval < 1.96 and MAPE < 10%, satisfying the pre-established acceptance criteria. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the regulatory submission requirements and the clinical failure mode of construct fatigue.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs — construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement — are the primary outputs required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw systems and directly characterize the structural performance relevant to the clinical failure mode of construct fatigue and loosening. Required level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
